7ed98f7b-0913-46dd-b838-740328d1bba9.0fc04009-e29c-4ff4-b323-58822a8fc99c.callout=snapshot-autodelete-set-option.pl 7ed98f7b-0913-46dd-b838-740328d1bba9.18d96cac-5fc2-4cc9-a269-c22960259e18.description=
Useful Op to keep a running results.
Takes a string input (resultText) and appends this to a global context key of "runningResults". As a result, the context key whose name is in the keyName input will be appended with the string from the input resultText.

Input Parameters\:
keyName - name of context key to append to
resultText - string input to append
delimiter - (leave blank for none) the delimiter to put between what is already in keyName before appending resultText

Responses\:
success - assigned the context variable

Returns\:
The the value of the context variable it appended to.

Context\:
runningResults

Scriptlet Example\:
currentResults \= scriptletContext.get("runningResults");

if (currentResults \=\= null) {
   currentResults \= resultText;
} else {
   currentResults +\= resultText;
}


scriptletContext.putGlobal("runningResults", currentResults);

7ed98f7b-0913-46dd-b838-740328d1bba9.dbc7a255-c0c6-4e80-99ba-3ce1a9b1faf8.callout=reformat snapshotAutodeleteOptionOptargs 7ed98f7b-0913-46dd-b838-740328d1bba9.dd04b75f-6886-439c-b652-0ebeb60ee76f.callout=grab volume-autosize config values 7ed98f7b-0913-46dd-b838-740328d1bba9.description=
Synopsis

    This flow configures a volume with different options, including SIS and snapshot.
    getVolApiConfig performs the following steps\:
      1. Retrieve the protocol volume style.
      2. Retrieve the security rules and permissions of the volume type.
      3. Retrieve the API volume by the volume type.
      4. Enable and set the configurations for a single instance storage (SIS) volume. This is a volume that contains NetApp deduplication.
      5. Set the volume with implementation-related options.
      6. Reformat the volume options.
      7. Set the snapshot auto-delete options on the volume.
      8. Reformat the snapshot auto-delete options.
      9. Set the volume autosize configurations.
    10. Pass the information to the requesting entity.

Inputs

    tier - The tier is the Quality of Service (QoS) offering for the product (e.g. vital, velocity, or value). The volume is assigned a storage tier that correlates to a service level and performance guarantee (required).
    protocol - The protocol of the volume (CIFS, NAS, etc.). A protocol relates to the operating system utilized in storage deployment (required).
    volumeTypeFs - The type of volume that is configured. Volume type is based on the rules and permissions surrounding the volume (required).
      Valid values\: Implementation-specific.
      Default value\: None.

    overrideJRAS - Value to override the system defined Java RAS server.
      Valid values\: Implementation specific.
      Default value\: Hosting Eng RAS.

Results

    hpooFlowResult - The XML response specific to the functionality of the flow; in this case a configured volume.  See Notes section for more details.
    flowStatus - Overall status of the flow, value is one of the string literals "success" or "failed".

Responses

    Success - All operations and subflows completed successfully.
    Failure - Some operations and/or subflows failed.

Notes

    1. Anything else the caller or support person may need to know about the flow. Relationships that aren't easily inferred, abmnormal flow behaviors, hard-codings, etc.
